<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Rider" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Rider,</orth> one who rides: <bibl n="shak. ven 40" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 40" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 40</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 40" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 40</bibl> <bibl n="shak. son 50.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 50, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lc 107" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 107</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 2.121" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 121</bibl> (with a pun; cf. <emph>Ride</emph> 2b). <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.131" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 131</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 2, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.7.24" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 7, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.4.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 4, 39</bibl>. == one who breaks in horses: <cit><quote>they are taught their manage, and to that end --s dearly hired,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 14</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>